Dexie only cares about the keypaths. If you&#39;ve created your DB outside Dexie and want to go over to using Dexie, it will adapt to using the exising indexes you&#39;ve created no matter what names you&#39;ve given them. Just specify the keypaths and Dexie will find the indexes.

Based on how you created your db and indexes, the corresponding dexie code would be:

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const db = new Dexie(&quot;myDB&quot;);

    db.version(0.1).stores({
      detailsTable: &quot;detail_id, survey_status, user_wave_id, dirty_bit&quot;
    });

The reason for using version(0.1) instead of just version(1) is described here: https://dexie.org/docs/Tutorial/Migrating-existing-DB-to-Dexie

